FBIS4-37545 "drnes120_k_94013" FBIS-NES-94-120 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 IRAQ PUK Attack Against IMP, KDP Forces Repelled PUK Attack Against IMP, KDP Forces Repelled LD1806142494 Tehran IRNA in English 1350 GMT 18 Jun 94 LD1806142494 Tehran IRNA English BFN [Text] Sanandaj, Kurdistan Prov., June 18, IRNA -- The Islamic Movement Party (IMP) and Kurdistan Democratic Party (KDP) of Iraq repelled an attack by Patriotic Union of Kurdistan (PUK) forces on their joint base in Asous region Friday, an IMP spokesman said here Saturday. According to the spokesman after being repelled, the PUK forces had reported to Iraq's National Congress troops stationed in the buffer zone between the belligerent parties, that the IMP-KDP forces had intended to attack them. Since the establishment of a ceasefire and deployment of Iraq's National Congress troops, the PUK forces have repeatedly violated the ceasefire under various pretexts, the spokesman added. PUK holds the view that Badenban region in the north and Souran in the south of Kurdistan should be partitioned and Kurdistan be administered as favored by the PUK.
